cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is about single image deraining, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel net that utilizes constrained transfer learning and circulatory structure, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper contributes a new paired rain image dataset, which could potentially place it in the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing, which could also place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
